08/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police detained the former owner of Meridian Bank on suspicion of privatisation fraud on Friday (August 6th).
Tomislav Djordjevic was arrested along with six other people.
The group allegedly siphoned off 3m euros after embezzling 60% of Ribarsko Gazdinstvo assets during the privatisation of the company.
(B92, Tanjug, Beta, RTS - 06/08/10)
